    <notes>While Chile traces its status as an independent nation back to 1810, it was only
        independent for four years before Spain reconquered it in 1814. From 1814 to 1818, Chile was
        reincorporated into the Viceroyalty of Peru, where it remained a colony until regaining its
        independence from Spain in 1818. U.S. recognized independence in 1823.</notes>
